title: Chocolate
body: Chocolate doesn't ask questions. Chocolate understands.

title: Eleanor
body: No one can make you feel inferior without your consent
author: Eleanor Roosevelt

title: Queen
body: Think like a queen. A queen is not afraid to fail. Failure is another steppingstone to greatness.
author: Oprah Winfrey

title: Unique
body: Always remember that you are absolutely unique. Just like everyone else.
author: Margaret Mead

title: Lemons
body: I believe that if life gives you lemons, you should make lemonade... And try to find somebody whose life has given them vodka, and have a party.
author: Ron White

title: Night
body: A day without sunshine is like, you know, night.
author: Steve Martin

title: Sails
body: I can't change the direction of the wind, but I can adjust my sails to always reach my destination
author: Jimmy Dean

title: Impossible
body: Start by doing what's necessary; then do what's possible; and suddenly you are doing the impossible
author: Francis of Assisi
